# Hits Prediction Model — The Muskets Football

## Overview

Build a machine-learning regression pipeline to predict the **`Hits`** column (how many times a player's page was viewed/searched) from the cleaned dataset `Muskets_data_cleaned.csv` (19 021 rows × 80 columns).

Because `Hits` is highly right-skewed (median = 5, max = 8 400), we will model **log1p(Hits)** and back-transform predictions.

---

## Dataset Summary

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Rows | 19 021 |
| Target (`Hits`) non-null | 16 426 (2 595 missing → dropped from training) |
| Target range | 1 – 8 400 (heavily skewed) |
| Numeric predictors | ~62 columns |
| Categorical predictors | `Nationality`, `Preferred Foot`, `A/W`, `D/W`, `Contract Status`, `Best Position`, `Positions` |

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Feature Engineering & Preprocessing

Drop: `ID`, `Name`, `LongName`, `photoUrl`, `playerUrl`, `Contract`, `Joined`, `Loan Date End` (leakage / identifiers / high-cardinality free text).

**Numeric features** (impute median):
All skill ratings, physical attributes, financial values, stats totals, `W/F`, `SM`, `IR`, `PAC`, `SHO`, `PAS`, `DRI`, `DEF`, `PHY`, `Age`, `Height`, `Weight`, `Value`, `Wage`, `Release Clause`, `Contract Start`, `Contract End`.

**Categorical features** (OrdinalEncoder / one-hot):
`Preferred Foot`, `A/W`, `D/W`, `Contract Status`, `Best Position`, `Nationality` (frequency encoded).

**Target transform**: `log1p(Hits)` → predict → `expm1()` to recover raw hits.

---

### 2. Models

| Model | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **Random Forest** | Robust baseline, handles mixed types, gives feature importance |
| **Gradient Boosting (XGBoost / LightGBM)** | Best tabular regression performance |
| **Linear Regression (Ridge)** | Interpretable baseline comparison |

Cross-validation: **5-fold KFold** on training set.

